data.title: Era ends as Dame Pattie Menzies dies at age of 96
data.meta_description: IT IS the end of an era. Dame Pattie Menzies, the wife of Australia's longest serving prime minister and Liberal Party founder Sir Robert Menzies, died yesterday in Canberra, aged 96.
data.text:
IT IS the end of an era. Dame Pattie Menzies, the wife of Australia's longest serving prime minister and Liberal Party founder Sir Robert Menzies, died yesterday in Canberra, aged 96.

Dame Pattie was a Liberal Party stalwart, its unofficial queen, talisman and a link with the happiest days of the party's life - the 1950s.
